From 1463bb3a5597a05f5d5efa893c7e35cef6d6f4af Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cole Walker <cole.walker@windriver.com>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 15:03:49 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 13/14] unicast_client: centralize FSM transitions and add unit
 tests

All raw ucma->state assignments replaced with a single transition
dispatcher unicast_client_do_transition(). This ensures side-effects
(clearing grants, resetting timers, triggering BMCA re-evaluation)
happen consistently regardless of which code path triggers the
transition.

Key changes:
- unicast_client_do_transition(): exit actions (TX CANCEL, clear
  granted bits) and entry actions (zero renewal_tmo, clock_set_sde)
  on every state change through one call site.
- unicast_client_reset(): called from port_initialize() for fault
  recovery — clears all per-master FSM state so stale grants don't
  survive a FAULTY->LISTENING->SLAVE cycle.
- Forced UC_WAIT->UC_NEED_SYDY with implicit ANNOUNCE grant bit
  when BMCA selects a master before the announce grant arrives.
- Grant rejection bypasses do_transition() intentionally (no CANCEL
  needed when server already denied service).

Unit tests: test_unicast_fsm.c (30 cases) covering full state x event
matrix, cancel from every state, lifecycle, rapid failover, and
regression cases from field bugs.

Replaces bullseye patches: 0078, 0082 (items 1, 3)

Signed-off-by: Cole Walker <cole.walker@windriver.com>
